This paper involves the use of deep learning algorithms for image analysis, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the study involves the validation and comparison of algorithm performance with human graders, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The study also involves the analysis of a large-scale clinical population, which could fall under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the study involves the use of reference standards and the evaluation of algorithm performance, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
